# API Rules — EGX Pro Backend

---

## 1. Route Structure

كل route لازم يكون بالترتيب ده بالظبط: method → path → middleware → controller

```ts
// ✅ CORRECT
import { Router } from 'express';
import { authenticate } from '../middleware/auth';
import { GoalsController } from '../controllers/goals.controller';

const router = Router();

router.get('/',              authenticate, GoalsController.list);
router.post('/',             authenticate, GoalsController.create);
router.put('/:id',           authenticate, GoalsController.update);
router.patch('/:id/amount',  authenticate, GoalsController.updateAmount);
router.delete('/:id',        authenticate, GoalsController.delete);

export default router;

// ❌ WRONG — business logic داخل الـ route مباشرة
router.post('/', authenticate, async (req, res) => {
  const count = await prisma.goal.count({ where: { userId: req.user.id } });
  if (count >= 3) return res.status(403).json({ error: 'limit' });
  const goal = await prisma.goal.create({ data: req.body });
  res.json(goal);
});
```

